{
  "texts": [
    "The pseudo-code for Semantic-Based Example Selection is summarized in Algorithm 1.",
    "Figure 5 shows an example of user prompt of Few-Shot ADL-LLM.",
    "4 Experimental Evaluation 4.1 Datasets Algorithm 1 Semantic-based Example SelectionWe evaluated ADL-LLM using two public datasets: MARBLE [4] and UCI ADL [39].",
    "We chose these datasets because they include sensor data from a wide variety of sensors (e.g., magnetic, plug, motion) that we are currently considering on a project involving data collection in the homes of subjects with Mild Cognitive Impairment (MCI).",
    "While the majority of works in the literature utilize the well-known CASAS datasets [18], which primarily include data from motion sensors, these datasets are limited in their ability to precisely characterize the specific activities performed by subjects."
  ]
}